# YouTube Cookies Configuration
# 
# Option 1: File-based cookies (for local development)
# 1. Export cookies from your browser using a browser extension like "Get cookies.txt"
# 2. Rename this file to cookies.txt
# 3. Place it in the project root directory
#
# Option 2: Environment variable (for Vercel deployment)
# 1. Export cookies from your browser using a browser extension
# 2. Base64 encode the cookies content:
#    - On Linux/Mac: base64 -w 0 cookies.txt
#    - On Windows: [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("cookies.txt"))
# 3. Set the YOUTUBE_COOKIES_B64 environment variable in Vercel with the base64 string
#
# For more information, see:
# https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/wiki/FAQ#how-do-i-pass-cookies-to-yt-dlp
# https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/wiki/Extractors#exporting-youtube-cookies
